    "asOf": "2019-01-28",
    "date": "2019-06-21T16:23:57Z",
    "text": "Robo Calls Off Phones Act or the Robo COP Act\n\nThis bill directs the Federal Trade Commission to revise the do-not-call registry provisions of the Telemarketing Sales Rule to prohibit politically-oriented recorded message telephone calls to telephone numbers listed on that registry.\n\nA \"politically-oriented recorded message telephone call\" is an outbound telephone call that plays a recorded message that (1) promotes, advertises, campaigns, or solicits donations for or against a political candidate or regarding a political issue; or (2) uses a political candidate's name."
  },
